Be2 Nc5 10. Nf2 { Supporting e4. } 10... e6 11. dxe6
{ This was an alternative given by me in my 1. d4 repertoire. White intends to complete development, castle long and then launch a kingside attack. }
11... fxe6 12. Be3 b6 13. Qc2 Bb7 14. O-O-O Nfd7
{ Intending ...Bxc3, which exploits the pressure on e4 to double White's c-pawns. }
15. h4 Bxc3 16. bxc3 e5 17. f5
{ This was played in the game -  (51)  Cheparinov,I  (2703)  -Najer,E  (2706)  Kocaeli 2017. Black played 17... gxf5 in the game, but I think an improvement is }
17... Nf6
{ Hitting e4. The position remains pretty unclear, but there are plenty of chances here for both sides. }
