7. bxc3 c5 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc4 Nc6 10. Nfe5
{ Note this position can also arise after 9. Ne5. } 10... Be6
{ This move has a couple of points. Attacking the knight on c4 is useful tactically in many variations, and also the bishop can come to d5 to neutralise white's fianchettoed bishop. }
11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Ne5 Nd5 13. Bd2 cxd4 14. cxd4 Rc8
{ Black has a couple of ideas here. ...c5 is of course in the works, and if white plays f4 then trading off light bishops with ...Nb6 + ...Bd5 is strong. }
