11. Nd2 Rc8 12. e4
{ This has been the most common move, but it is in fact an error. } 12... Bg4
13. f3 cxd4 { A brilliant tactical idea. } 14. cxd4 Be6
{ It is important that white's pawn was lured to f3 so that black has ...Qb6+ after d5. }
15. Nb3 Ne8 { Attacking d4  (...Bxb3+ is threatened)  . } 16. e5 b6
{ White's central pawn mass has been lured forward, and the next step is to blockade it on the d5 square using ...Nc6-b4-d5. }
