{ The correct moveorder. Playing 5...O-O and white responding with 6. cxd5 would not allow my suggested line against the Nf3+ cxd5 mainline. }
6. Na3 c3
{ The true Grunfeld move. It has gradually overtaken the O-O 7.O-O Nc6 8. Nxc4 Be6 line. The c3 line does strengthen the white centre, but it also comes with a few advantages. It closes the c file and means that c3 becomes a possible target for black. Due to this c4 becomes a key square and a big goal in black's plan is to occupy it with a piece, usually the knight. Black wants to play actively here with c5, but must be careful not to allow the advance of pawns to e4, d5 and c4 respectively. }
