11. Bb2 { Note that this position can arise after both 10. Bb2 and 10. Qe2. }
11... Qb6
{ Often this is a great square for the queen. It puts pressure on the bishop, prepares ...Rfd8 and if white wants to kick the queen away with Nc4 then the pin after ...Qa6 is irrititating. }
12. d5
{ White makes use of a little tactical idea to gain some space and free his dark bishop. }
12... Na5 13. c4 Qb4
{ With the queen on b4, attacking Na3, a number of tactical ideas present themselves. For example, black threatens ...Nxd5 ! now. }
14. Nh4 Be4 15. f3 Nd7 { ...Qb4 turned out to be very useful. } 16. Bxg7 Kxg7
17. fxe4 Qxa3 18. Nf3 { White threatens e5. } 18... f6
{ Good positional chess. Next comes ... Ne5, fixing white's pawns on the light squares. }
