11. exd5 Bf5
{ The bishop is good here. d3 is taken under control, so ...Na6-b4-d3 is possible later on, and ...Qd7 + ...Bh3 is another idea. }
12. h3
{ White is obviously a bit worried about that bishop so he intends to kick it away with g4. }
12... h5 { Black should of course prevent this if possible. } 13. Ne4 Bxe4
{ It's a pity to surrender the bishop pair, but it does gain black a lot of time to get his knights to good squares. }
14. Bxe4 Nc8
{ Other moves are good too, but I like this with the simple idea of the ...Nd6 blockade. }
15. Bg2 Nd6
{ Black has fully equalised here - the bishop pair doesn't count for much when the knights have great squares. }
*

