11. Qc2 { This seems like quite a natural square for white's queen. } 11... a4
{ A simple space-gaining move. The rook is free to enter the game via a5 now. }
12. Rd1 Bf5
{ This is played with the standard idea of luring white's e4-pawn forward. }
13. Qe2 Qc8
{ An important idea. The point is to secure the bishop's square on g4 without any h3 disturbances. Black will play either ...Bg4 or ...e5 next. }
