11... Be6
{ Taking control of some light squares, especially c4. Black will try to harass white's queen with ...Bc4, and in the event of Qc2, then ...Nb4 can be considered. }
12. Rd1
{ This was the main move until white realised it was better to prevent ...Bc4. }
12... Bc4 13. Qc2 Nb4 { Constantly attacking the queen. } 14. Qb1 e5 15. a3
exd4 16. axb4 dxc3
{ Black sacrifices some material temporarily for massive threats on white's back rank. }
17. Rxd8 Raxd8
{ ...Rd1+ is threatened, which white can't preventing without losing further material. Best is 18. bxc3 after which black can take a perpetual if he wants to or he can keep playing. }
