6... Qxd5 7. Ne2 O-O 8. Nc3 Qd8
{ The queen can retreat to a number of squares, but this is the simplest. It gets out of the way and plans ...c5. }
9. Be2 c5 { Playing for ... e5 is another decent possibility. } 10. d5 e6 11.
e4 exd5 12. exd5 b6 13. O-O Bb7
{ Black has a good position here. This is a fairly standard Grunfeld structure, but black has a nice version here since he is so well developed. }
