{ The Russian System. White practically forces black to give up the centre with dxc4 and follows up with e4, grabbing the whole centre himself. Black has many, many possible options against this, including  (after ...dxc4 and ...O-O)  ...Na6, ...a6, ...Nc6 + ...Bg4 etc. My choice will be a cutting edge gambit line based on ...Nc6 and ...e5 which sacrifices a pawn or two in exchange for massive activity. The line is theoretically sound, interesting and gives black a positive win rate. }
