Bd3
{ This is logical. It protects e4 but more importantly prepares to castle. This means black needs to act quickly. }
15... a5 { Black is of course preparing ...b4. } 16. Qf4
{ This move is also logically protecting e4. } 16... b4 17. Ne2 Rb8
{ This is played with the simple idea of exchanging bishops  (the defender of e4)  . }
18. f3 Bb5 19. Bxb5 Rxb5
{ White has reached a delicate position. Black is very active and has a number of tactical ideas on the e-file   for example,  20.O-O  Nxd5 !  . }
