15... a5 { Black is of course preparing ...b4. } 16. f3 { Securing e4. } 16...
Nh5 { Planning ...f5. } 17. Be3 b4 18. Ne2 Bxb2 19. Rb1 Be5 20. Qb6 Bc7
{ White's exposed queen and the fact that it can't escape allows black a perpetual. However, if you need to play for a win, f5 is good too. }
