19... b4 { Kicking this knight back makes sense. } 20. Nd1 Bxg3 21. hxg3 Nxg3
{ Black is down a piece and a pawn, but there are threats aplenty and white simply can't get more than a perpetual - ...Qh4 is on its way. }
22. Ba6 { 22. Qf2 would be met with the idea of ...Rxc1 followed by ...Qg5 !. }
22... fxe4 23. Bxc8 Qh4 24. Qxd7 Qh1+ 25. Kf2 Qxf3+
{ Black, while being down a rook and 2 bishops, secures the perpetual. } *

