16. g4 { White tries to activate his dark bishop with f5. } 16... Qf6 17. Bb2
c4
{ A nice thematic move. A strong but complicated and risky alternative is ...Qd6 followed by ...Re8. Black's idea here is to simply keep the a1-h8 diagonal blocked off. Black exploits the fact that the bishop on e2 is tied to the defence of g4. }
18. f5 { gxf5 in these types of positions seems to always be dubious. } 18...
b5
{ Solidifying the c4-pawn. Now the bishop on b2 will be out of play for a long time. }
19. fxg6 Qxg6
{ The position remains complicated but white's king is inb more danger than black's. }
